\end_layout

\end_inset

 provide a comprehensive review of the statistical approaches used to analyze text from reputation systems and social media. The second approach is grounded in consumer behavior theory and starts by forming a hypothesis regarding the effects of specific text constructs. The presence of constructs in text is often detected manually (
\emph on
e.g.
\emph default
, using human coders), or via simple pattern matching rules.
\end_layout

